    {
      "id": "c746ab38-a189-4540-b7f6-bccf7462d004",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $f(x,y)=2e^{-x}e^{-2y}\\textbf{1}_{(\\R^+)^2}(x,y)$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(f(x,y)=2e^{-x}e^{-2y}\\textbf{1}_{(\\R^+)^2}(x,y)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "83a8992e-7b1b-48ff-abf9-01707bcff1d0",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Vérifier que $f$ définit une densité de probabilité.",
        "html": "<p>Vérifier que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> définit une\ndensité de probabilité.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2b836295-2cfe-4f69-92ed-4f53cb1ac5eb",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On vérifie que $f$ est positive sur $\\R^2$ et par application du théorème de Fubini que $\\int_{-\\infty}^{+\\infty}\\int_{-\\infty}^{+\\infty} f(x,y) dxdy=1$",
        "html": "<p>On vérifie que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> est positive\nsur <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\R^2\\)</span> et par application du\nthéorème de Fubini que <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\int_{-\\infty}^{+\\infty}\\int_{-\\infty}^{+\\infty}\nf(x,y) dxdy=1\\)</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2e6f70b9-34dc-49ed-9b8f-984315335672",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Calculer $\\PP(X>1,Y<1)$, $\\PP(X<Y)$ et $\\PP(X<a)$.",
        "html": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\PP(X&gt;1,Y&lt;1)\\)</span>,\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\PP(X&lt;Y)\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\PP(X&lt;a)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "180531f3-a5d8-432a-b7b6-57e3df44f14c",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On applique la définition et on trouve $\\PP(X>1,Y<1) = e^{-1}(1-e^{-2})$, $\\PP(X<Y)=\\frac{1}{3}$ et $\\PP(X<a)=1-e^{-a}$.",
        "html": "<p>On applique la définition et on trouve <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\PP(X&gt;1,Y&lt;1) = e^{-1}(1-e^{-2})\\)</span>,\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\PP(X&lt;Y)=\\frac{1}{3}\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\PP(X&lt;a)=1-e^{-a}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
  "preview": "<p>Soit <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(f(x,y)=2e^{-x}e^{-2y}\\textbf{1}_{(\\R^+)^2}(x,y)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
